WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:04.250
Kevin: My life
was going pretty terrible.

00:04.250 --> 00:06.620
I lost my job, had to move in
with my sister and my niece.

00:06.620 --> 00:08.880
And then, things got weird.

00:08.880 --> 00:10.120
I wouldn't do that.

00:12.380 --> 00:13.750
Super weird.

00:13.750 --> 00:15.210
-Am I still asleep?
-No.

00:15.210 --> 00:18.420
In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:18.420 --> 00:20.540
You are the last
of the righteous.

00:20.540 --> 00:23.420
You are on a mission to bring
balance to the Universe.

00:23.420 --> 00:26.000
Who are you talking to?
She can't see me.

00:26.000 --> 00:29.580
She's done a pretty good job
convincing me she's real.

00:29.580 --> 00:31.330
You don't make
protecting you easy.

00:31.330 --> 00:34.460
And now I have to do something
I haven't had to do before --

00:34.460 --> 00:37.710
put others before myself,
help people.

00:37.710 --> 00:40.380
I am the last guy you'd
ever want to save the world,

00:40.380 --> 00:42.290
but I think
I can figure it out...

00:42.290 --> 00:43.080
probably.

00:45.880 --> 00:47.580
Did that meteor
give you superpowers?

00:50.540 --> 00:51.580
Did it?

00:51.580 --> 00:52.920
Uh, superpowers?

00:52.920 --> 00:56.540
That's -- What's so --
Why would you even ask that?

00:56.540 --> 00:58.790
Because I've seen
weird stuff.

00:58.790 --> 01:00.540
Reese, you have --
That's not...

01:00.540 --> 01:03.040
[ Stammers ]

01:03.040 --> 01:06.710
Reese, that is the craziest
thing that I have ever heard.

01:06.710 --> 01:08.670
Do I have superpowers?

01:08.670 --> 01:10.290
First of all,
if I did have superpowers,

01:10.290 --> 01:11.750
do you think I would be
keeping it a secret?

01:11.750 --> 01:13.790
Reese: I knew he wouldn't
give me a straight answer.

01:13.790 --> 01:15.750
...kind of hurts my feelings
'cause I've always
wanted superpowers...

01:15.750 --> 01:17.170
But that's fine.

01:17.170 --> 01:18.750
He already told me
everything I need to know.

01:18.750 --> 01:22.540
...trying to, like, live in
the world with normal powers,

01:22.540 --> 01:24.330
not even -- I don't even
have normal powers.

01:24.330 --> 01:26.170
The more he talks
like a crazy person...

01:26.170 --> 01:29.210
...medium-regular-guy
type of thing...

01:29.210 --> 01:31.250
...the more I know
I'm closer to the truth.

01:31.250 --> 01:33.620
...because if you're not
hydrated, then you can
start to see things...

01:33.620 --> 01:35.790
Something happened
the night the meteor fell.

01:35.790 --> 01:37.500
There was a guy who thought
he had superpowers

01:37.500 --> 01:39.040
'cause he was on drugs,
and he jumped off a cliff.

01:39.040 --> 01:40.500
And I have a theory.

01:42.080 --> 01:45.000
It's the classic
origin story.

01:45.000 --> 01:46.710
Meteor falls to Earth...

01:46.710 --> 01:48.420
I wouldn't touch it!

01:48.420 --> 01:49.710
...normal idiot touches it.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.210
[ Kevin screams ]

01:51.210 --> 01:54.250
Idiot acts weird, heads home,

01:54.250 --> 01:57.500
goes to sleep,
and then the changes begin.

01:57.500 --> 02:05.750
♪♪

02:05.750 --> 02:13.920
♪♪

02:13.920 --> 02:17.040
[ Whirring ]

02:17.040 --> 02:19.330
Idiot will never be
the same again.

02:19.330 --> 02:22.920
♪♪

02:22.920 --> 02:25.960
♪ Eating breakfast,
eating breakfast ♪

02:25.960 --> 02:27.460
[ Clicks tongue ]

02:27.460 --> 02:30.210
But what kind of powers
does he have?

02:30.210 --> 02:32.580
I've already seen a couple.

02:32.580 --> 02:35.580
[ Tires screech ]
[ Grunts ]

02:35.580 --> 02:37.210
He might be immortal.

02:38.960 --> 02:41.500
He can definitely float
in thin air.

02:41.500 --> 02:43.210
♪ Goes right in my tummy ♪

02:43.210 --> 02:47.380
But is that all, or are there
more powers I haven't seen yet?

02:47.380 --> 02:49.380
Maybe he can move things
with his mind.

02:51.960 --> 02:53.540
♪ Tastes so good ♪

02:54.880 --> 02:57.830
Hey! Why?

02:57.830 --> 02:59.620
I thought you'd
stop it.

02:59.620 --> 03:02.210
How?

03:02.210 --> 03:04.080
You wasted all of
my favorite cereal.

03:09.670 --> 03:11.500
♪♪

03:11.500 --> 03:13.540
The meteor did
something to him...

03:17.460 --> 03:19.420
...and I'm gonna find out
what it is.

03:28.960 --> 03:31.460
[ Cellphone ringtone ]
♪ Hallelujah ♪

03:31.460 --> 03:33.790
♪ Hallelujah ♪

03:33.790 --> 03:35.540
♪ Hallelujah, hallelujah ♪

03:35.540 --> 03:38.000
Nope.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.250
Hey.

03:39.250 --> 03:40.580
I have certified mail

03:40.580 --> 03:42.000
for Kevin Finn.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.080
I can take it for him.

03:47.880 --> 03:55.960
♪♪

03:55.960 --> 03:57.210
Hey.

03:57.210 --> 03:59.670
[ Clears throat, sniffles ]

03:59.670 --> 04:01.880
Morning.

04:01.880 --> 04:03.170
You taking Reese to school
or what?

04:03.170 --> 04:04.880
She'll be late.

04:04.880 --> 04:08.080
Uh, no. She's off --
teacher conference day.

04:13.920 --> 04:16.540
Are you sad because my parents
used to dress us alike?

04:16.540 --> 04:20.580
Because I have about 15 years of
photos that will make you weep.

04:22.620 --> 04:25.420
You were darling...

04:25.420 --> 04:27.920
both of you.

04:27.920 --> 04:30.250
We still are.

04:30.250 --> 04:33.460
Time passes
so quickly here.

04:33.460 --> 04:35.790
And none of you realize it
until it's --

04:35.790 --> 04:38.330
it's too late.

04:38.330 --> 04:41.540
In a blink of an eye,
it's over.

04:41.540 --> 04:44.040
These two babies will never
exist again.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.290
Hey, are you okay?

04:48.290 --> 04:49.880
[ Sighs ]

04:49.880 --> 04:51.790
[ Knock on door ]
Reese: Kevin, you in there?

04:51.790 --> 04:54.080
Yeah. One second.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.040
Hey, Reese.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.040
Hi.

04:59.040 --> 05:01.580
You look...tired.

05:01.580 --> 05:04.170
Oh. Um, I'm not.

05:04.170 --> 05:06.460
Hmm.
Must just be your face.

05:06.460 --> 05:09.000
You knocked, right?

05:09.000 --> 05:10.460
Here, this just came
for you.

05:10.460 --> 05:11.790
Oh.

05:11.790 --> 05:13.960
So, what is it?

05:13.960 --> 05:17.210
It is my last severance check
from work.

05:17.210 --> 05:19.880
It's just in time --
the well was running dry.

05:19.880 --> 05:22.960
Now it's sushi for breakfast
every day.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.080
Is that a joke?

05:25.080 --> 05:27.040
I guess not.
[ Clears throat ]

05:29.620 --> 05:32.620
Can I ask you a question?
It's kind of important.

05:32.620 --> 05:34.580
[ Bell rings ]

05:34.580 --> 05:36.420
As you can see from
the quiz scores, Reese --

05:36.420 --> 05:38.290
she really started out
the term strong.

05:38.290 --> 05:39.580
Amy: That's great.

05:39.580 --> 05:41.330
Every time I ask her
how she's doing in school,

05:41.330 --> 05:43.460
all I get is "good."

05:43.460 --> 05:45.000
Eh. Well,
you know Reese.

05:45.000 --> 05:46.670
She does not like to be
the center of attention.

05:46.670 --> 05:47.830
No. [ Chuckles ]

05:47.830 --> 05:49.460
I -- Actually,
I-I found the place

05:49.460 --> 05:51.000
that she expresses
herself the best.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.250
It's -- It's
in her writing.

05:53.250 --> 05:55.580
Oh, yeah, I know. She's always
writing in that diary of hers.

05:55.580 --> 05:57.000
Oh. Sorry.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.330
She gets mad
when I call it that.

05:58.330 --> 05:59.330
Her journal.

05:59.330 --> 06:00.330
Well, that's actually --

06:00.330 --> 06:01.500
It's kind of why I'm excited

06:01.500 --> 06:02.250
to see how she does

06:02.250 --> 06:03.290
with this next assignment.

06:03.290 --> 06:06.380
The students will follow
and interview

06:06.380 --> 06:08.040
someone they admire,

06:08.040 --> 06:08.960
and then write their history.

06:08.960 --> 06:10.670
-Oh.
-Yeah.

06:10.670 --> 06:13.290
We're trying to teach them how,
oftentimes, history is shaped

06:13.290 --> 06:15.500
by the historian,
you know?

06:15.500 --> 06:18.000
Well, some of my work
is classified,

06:18.000 --> 06:21.670
but I still have some great
stuff for her to write about.

06:21.670 --> 06:23.080
[ Giggles ]

06:24.250 --> 06:26.880
Oh. Uh...

06:26.880 --> 06:29.790
Reese -- Reese said she was
gonna ask Kevin.

06:29.790 --> 06:34.000
Kevin? Oh!
[ Chuckles ] Great.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.500
Gr-- Great.
[ Laughs ]

06:36.500 --> 06:37.500
-Right?
-Kevin.

06:37.500 --> 06:38.540
She...

06:38.540 --> 06:39.540
That's great.

06:39.540 --> 06:40.620
Huh.

06:40.620 --> 06:41.960
Well, I'm sure
he'll be thrilled.

06:41.960 --> 06:43.330
No. Absolutely not.

06:43.330 --> 06:44.500
Come on! Please?

06:44.500 --> 06:46.790
You're not doing a report
on my life.

06:46.790 --> 06:48.170
Write about your mother.

06:48.170 --> 06:49.580
I already know
everything about her.

06:49.580 --> 06:50.920
That's boring.

06:50.920 --> 06:53.330
Please.
Your mom is so cool.

06:53.330 --> 06:55.460
Did you know she got all A's
until the 11th grade,

06:55.460 --> 06:57.420
which, as I say it,
doesn't sound cool,

06:57.420 --> 06:58.920
but you just need
to trust me.

06:58.920 --> 07:00.420
No, I don't.

07:00.420 --> 07:01.750
Well, the answer
is no, okay?

07:01.750 --> 07:03.710
Definitely no,
infinity no.

07:03.710 --> 07:06.170
Okay? Now, I got to run,
because I'm late now

07:06.170 --> 07:09.290
to do the...
things that I do.

07:09.290 --> 07:11.790
[ Door closes ]

07:11.790 --> 07:13.540
Reese is gonna be a problem.
[ Sighs ]

07:13.540 --> 07:16.250
I can't lie my way out
of what she's seen,

07:16.250 --> 07:17.500
so what should I do?

07:17.500 --> 07:19.830
She wants to grow up
so badly.

07:19.830 --> 07:21.170
Help her appreciate
her childhood

07:21.170 --> 07:23.500
while she still has it.

07:23.500 --> 07:25.040
Why are you so sad?

07:25.040 --> 07:26.540
Are you still homesick?

07:26.540 --> 07:30.710
Look, I'm not used to dealing
with all this human emotion.

07:30.710 --> 07:33.710
I mean, sadness,
fear, regret.

07:33.710 --> 07:36.000
It's this place.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.210
Mm. It's overwhelming.

07:38.210 --> 07:40.540
Can I do anything
to help?

07:40.540 --> 07:41.540
No.

07:41.540 --> 07:42.790
Focus on your job.

07:42.790 --> 07:44.170
I just --

07:44.170 --> 07:46.500
I just need to find
my inner peace.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.120
I know it's
in there somewhere.

07:48.120 --> 07:52.210
[ Inhales, exhales deeply ]

07:52.210 --> 07:54.330
Mm. There. Better.

07:54.330 --> 07:55.960
[ Electronic beeping ]
Oh. Easy.

07:55.960 --> 07:59.960
29 large is giving me so much
inner peace right now.

07:59.960 --> 08:02.580
Get out a sweet hundo
for myself.

08:02.580 --> 08:03.620
[ Machine whirring ]

08:07.380 --> 08:09.380
Um...

08:09.380 --> 08:10.960
What is it?

08:10.960 --> 08:15.290
$12 and a coupon
for lip balm?

08:15.290 --> 08:16.500
[ Whirring ]

08:16.500 --> 08:17.960
No! Come on!

08:17.960 --> 08:19.920
I want my money!

08:19.920 --> 08:21.790
[ Clicks tongue ]

08:21.790 --> 08:25.960
The Universe thinks
you need lip balm.

08:25.960 --> 08:27.290
Let's get some.

08:27.290 --> 08:30.290
But...money.

08:30.290 --> 08:31.170
[ Sighs ]

08:35.120 --> 08:37.420
I'm not sure what to do.

08:37.420 --> 08:42.080
Do I just, like...
buy $12 worth of these?

08:44.620 --> 08:47.670
Hey, um...quick work-related
question --

08:47.670 --> 08:49.040
are your lips dry?

08:50.620 --> 08:52.620
Rick: Ugh.
I left my wallet at home.

08:52.620 --> 08:53.790
I might have cash
in the car.

08:53.790 --> 08:55.880
Uh, how much is it?
-$13.46.

08:55.880 --> 08:57.830
[ Taps counter ]
I'm gonna have to run home.

08:57.830 --> 08:59.210
Uh, you know what?

08:59.210 --> 09:00.710
I -- Here, I'll get it.
[ Laughs ]

09:00.710 --> 09:02.290
-What?
-Yeah.

09:02.290 --> 09:03.670
No, uh, you don't
have to do that. That's fine.

09:03.670 --> 09:05.920
No, no, it's all good.
I even got a coupon.

09:05.920 --> 09:08.040
[ Chuckles ]

09:08.040 --> 09:10.040
[ Register beeps ]
Cashier: $12 even.

09:10.040 --> 09:13.620
Thank you.
That's so...nice.

09:13.620 --> 09:14.620
[ Chuckles ]
[ Register opens ]

09:14.620 --> 09:15.750
You're welcome.

09:15.750 --> 09:18.040
Uh, enjoy your
moist lips.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.790
And your, uh,
turkey jerky.

09:22.790 --> 09:25.000
[ Laughs ] I will.

09:25.000 --> 09:26.420
Thanks again.
-Mm-hmm.

09:27.880 --> 09:29.540
You want your receipt?

09:29.540 --> 09:31.710
Oh. Uh...ah, sure.
Thanks.

09:34.120 --> 09:37.330
Okay, we're done.
It's easy.

09:37.330 --> 09:40.750
I'm pretty sure
there's more to do.

09:44.420 --> 09:47.000
Oh.

09:47.000 --> 09:49.290
I have a bad feeling
about this.

09:49.290 --> 09:51.790
-What?
-Where this is going.

09:51.790 --> 09:54.000
The Universe is gonna make me
give away all my money.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.620
I can feel it.

09:55.620 --> 09:57.290
And why is that bad?

09:57.290 --> 09:59.250
Because it's my money.

09:59.250 --> 10:02.670
Kevin,
money is just paper.

10:02.670 --> 10:03.920
It's worthless.

10:03.920 --> 10:05.460
Actually,
that's not true.

10:05.460 --> 10:07.580
Um, it has a specific worth
written right on the bill.

10:07.580 --> 10:11.170
Worthless, unless you're
using it to spread joy.

10:11.170 --> 10:12.620
When you were
an investment banker,

10:12.620 --> 10:14.880
you hoarded money,
you worshiped it.

10:14.880 --> 10:17.250
How did it make you feel?

10:17.250 --> 10:18.540
Fine. Rich.

10:18.540 --> 10:20.330
Alone.

10:20.330 --> 10:21.880
Let's make up for that.

10:21.880 --> 10:23.920
This is the perfect time
for a lesson about

10:23.920 --> 10:26.000
the incredible rewards
you reap

10:26.000 --> 10:28.380
by simply being generous
to others.

10:28.380 --> 10:30.250
Fine. Let's --
Let's be generous.

10:30.250 --> 10:32.540
Let's...just do it.

10:32.540 --> 10:33.880
Yes.

10:33.880 --> 10:35.420
[ Electronic beeping ]

10:35.420 --> 10:37.330
What? I'm doing it.

10:39.040 --> 10:45.790
♪♪

10:45.790 --> 10:46.670
Popsicle stick?

