11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
♪ Hey ♪
♪ My cash machine ♪

11:34.000 --> 11:35.790
♪ Since that check came in ♪
[ Beeping ]

11:37.170 --> 11:39.380
Kevin: Free burritos.
Come get 'em.

11:39.380 --> 11:40.960
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪
Enjoy.

11:40.960 --> 11:42.170
[ Beeps ]

11:44.500 --> 11:48.170
Is that a prescription?
Can you read that?

11:48.170 --> 11:49.880
Hi.

11:49.880 --> 11:51.290
Just need to fill...

11:53.670 --> 11:56.750
...uh, that -- whatever that
writing says right there...

11:56.750 --> 11:58.670
for a loved one.

11:58.670 --> 12:02.170
Okay. Uh, can I see
your insurance card?

12:02.170 --> 12:04.120
Oh, I-I don't
have insurance.

12:04.120 --> 12:05.290
Oh, that's no problem.

12:05.290 --> 12:07.080
It'll just be a moment.
-All right.

12:10.080 --> 12:11.830
How do you feel?
[ Giggles ]

12:11.830 --> 12:13.460
Broke.

12:13.460 --> 12:15.250
Aw, come on!

12:15.250 --> 12:16.580
Deep down in your gut,

12:16.580 --> 12:19.040
how does it feel
to make those people happy?

12:19.040 --> 12:21.040
-Honestly?
-Yeah.

12:21.040 --> 12:22.880
It's pretty amazing.

12:22.880 --> 12:24.120
[ Laughs ]

12:24.120 --> 12:26.120
I know! I know!
[ Laughs ]

12:26.120 --> 12:28.710
So, uh...
what's my reward?

12:28.710 --> 12:30.330
Reward?

12:30.330 --> 12:33.040
Yeah. You said, um, there
would be "incredible rewards"

12:33.040 --> 12:34.960
once I gave
all my money away.

12:34.960 --> 12:36.500
Remember?

12:36.500 --> 12:38.960
Uh, yeah. This.

12:38.960 --> 12:41.750
This is the reward -- the way
you're feeling right now.

12:41.750 --> 12:43.080
-Right.
-Right.

12:43.080 --> 12:44.580
-Oh!
-[ Laughs ]

12:44.580 --> 12:46.120
Good.

12:46.120 --> 12:47.500
Good.

12:47.500 --> 12:50.620
Right.

12:50.620 --> 12:52.790
You thought the reward was
getting all your money back.

12:52.790 --> 12:53.880
I did. Kind of. Yeah.

12:53.880 --> 12:55.460
Kevin...

12:55.460 --> 12:57.830
think about all the good
you did today.

12:57.830 --> 12:59.500
Kindness is infectious.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.460
Now, the people you help
will be much more inclined

13:01.460 --> 13:03.120
to help someone else.

13:03.120 --> 13:04.460
Nifty.

13:04.460 --> 13:05.790
Pharmacist: Sir.

13:07.790 --> 13:11.210
Uh, without insurance,
your total is $540.

13:11.210 --> 13:13.040
Of course it is.

13:13.040 --> 13:16.420
That's all my money.

13:16.420 --> 13:18.670
[ Register beeps ]

13:18.670 --> 13:22.830
Insulin.
Maxwell Owens.

13:22.830 --> 13:24.880
Uh, hey! Sorry.

13:24.880 --> 13:27.460
Uh -- Uh,
we just moved.

13:27.460 --> 13:30.290
Do you have the, uh,
address on file?

13:30.290 --> 13:33.420
801 Creek Lane.
801 Creek Lane.

13:33.420 --> 13:34.460
[ Doorbell rings ]

13:39.580 --> 13:42.170
Hi. Is, uh --
Is Maxwell home?

13:42.170 --> 13:43.880
I-I'm Max.

13:43.880 --> 13:47.920
Oh, good.
Um, this is for you.

13:47.920 --> 13:48.920
Who are you?

13:48.920 --> 13:50.250
-Uh...I --
-Hi.

13:50.250 --> 13:51.960
-Hi.
-Can I help you?

13:51.960 --> 13:54.040
He brought me
my insulin.

13:54.040 --> 13:55.120
What?

13:55.120 --> 13:56.420
[ Bag rustles ]

13:56.420 --> 13:57.460
Max, go inside.

14:00.540 --> 14:01.750
What the hell
is this about?

14:01.750 --> 14:03.040
Um, nothing.

14:03.040 --> 14:04.920
I'm just a --
just a friend, kind of.

14:04.920 --> 14:07.460
You're a grown man giving drugs
to a teenage boy.

14:07.460 --> 14:08.960
What? Ew. No.

14:08.960 --> 14:10.330
That sounds gross
when you say it like that.

14:10.330 --> 14:11.420
Okay, I don't know
what you're up to,

14:11.420 --> 14:12.500
but I want nothing
to do with it.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.920
[ Bag rustles ]
Okay. But still -- here.

14:13.920 --> 14:15.460
No.
Well...

14:15.460 --> 14:16.460
you -- you have to take it.

14:16.460 --> 14:17.460
No, I don't have to
do anything.

14:17.460 --> 14:18.670
-I'm just trying to help.
-We don't want your help.

14:18.670 --> 14:19.750
But I --

14:23.880 --> 14:25.540
Reese, come on!
You're gonna be late for school.

14:25.540 --> 14:28.330
What kind of mother turns down
medication for her son?

14:28.330 --> 14:31.960
[ Sighs ] A good one?
She's not wrong.

14:31.960 --> 14:34.420
I am a total stranger
offering her kid drugs.

14:34.420 --> 14:35.670
Mnh-mnh, mnh-mnh.

14:35.670 --> 14:38.000
I'm -- I'm feeling...

14:38.000 --> 14:39.380
I don't know
what this is.

14:41.000 --> 14:43.500
Frustrated.
I'm feeling frustrated.

14:43.500 --> 14:45.290
-Mm.
-It's very unpleasant.

14:45.290 --> 14:47.420
Yeah. That's pretty much
my baseline.

14:47.420 --> 14:48.750
How are you supposed
to help someone

14:48.750 --> 14:50.670
when they won't
accept it?

14:50.670 --> 14:52.750
Some people are too proud
to admit they need help,

14:52.750 --> 14:55.290
that...they think it means
they're weak.

14:55.290 --> 14:57.790
I get that.
I've done that.

14:57.790 --> 15:00.500
I don't get it.

15:00.500 --> 15:02.710
Look...

15:02.710 --> 15:04.330
it's a setback.

15:04.330 --> 15:06.210
But we just have to
figure out another way

15:06.210 --> 15:07.210
to get the medicine
to him.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.710
No. Forget it.

15:08.710 --> 15:10.500
We're not spending
any more time on this.

15:10.500 --> 15:12.540
Mnh-mnh.
[ Scoffs ]

15:12.540 --> 15:15.790
Okay, I know that you -- you're
new to feelings and everything,

15:15.790 --> 15:19.120
but -- but this is clearly
your emotions talking.

15:19.120 --> 15:21.290
-I want them to shut up.
-[ Chuckles ]

15:21.290 --> 15:22.670
Well, you could try
to do what I do

15:22.670 --> 15:24.920
and stuff it all down
into a dark, terrible place

15:24.920 --> 15:27.040
and deal with it
in therapy later.

15:27.040 --> 15:28.750
It's great advice.

15:28.750 --> 15:30.330
That is great advice.

15:32.670 --> 15:34.830
Hey! Hi.
Ready for school?

15:37.250 --> 15:39.040
Let's go.

15:39.040 --> 15:41.080
Okay.

15:41.080 --> 15:42.830
[ Truck doors opening ]

15:45.750 --> 15:47.120
What is this?

15:47.120 --> 15:49.170
Oh, that's...
just some medicine

15:49.170 --> 15:50.750
I had to pick up
for a friend.

15:50.750 --> 15:53.290
You know Max Owens?

15:53.290 --> 15:55.250
Do you know him?

15:55.250 --> 15:56.830
I know who he is.

15:56.830 --> 15:58.420
He goes to my school.

15:58.420 --> 16:00.210
Oh, my God.
That is great.

16:00.210 --> 16:03.250
Would you give that to him
for me?

16:03.250 --> 16:05.000
[ Engine starts ]
No.
Why?

16:05.000 --> 16:07.080
Because. No.
It's weird.

16:08.290 --> 16:09.670
[ Engine shuts off ]

16:09.670 --> 16:12.120
Okay.

16:12.120 --> 16:14.540
I will you let you do
your report on me.

16:16.880 --> 16:18.460
Seriously?

16:18.460 --> 16:19.830
Yes.

16:19.830 --> 16:22.170
You can interview me,
ask me anything,

16:22.170 --> 16:25.170
as long as you get
that medicine to Max.

16:25.170 --> 16:26.830
I mean, I [Sighs]

16:26.830 --> 16:28.540
I don't even know him.

16:28.540 --> 16:29.960
So?

16:29.960 --> 16:31.170
You don't have to
make out with the guy.

16:31.170 --> 16:34.000
-Shut up.
-Reese.

16:34.000 --> 16:37.830
Think about all of the
amazing, interesting things

16:37.830 --> 16:40.080
I have to tell you
about my life --

16:40.080 --> 16:42.420
so many secrets
to share.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.290
-Fine.
-Great.

16:47.790 --> 16:50.170
I'm interviewing
you tonight.

16:50.170 --> 16:52.500
I'm unavailable,
actually, ton-- Ow.

16:52.500 --> 16:54.790
[ Engine starts ]

16:54.790 --> 16:58.420
♪♪

16:58.420 --> 17:03.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:03.420 --> 17:05.120
[ Bell rings ]

17:11.790 --> 17:13.620
Max?

17:13.620 --> 17:15.420
-Yeah?
-Hi.

17:15.420 --> 17:17.960
Um...sorry.

17:17.960 --> 17:22.540
Um, Kevin, my uncle, wanted me
to give this to you.

17:22.540 --> 17:23.790
So...

17:23.790 --> 17:25.540
That guy was
your uncle?

17:25.540 --> 17:27.920
Yeah.

17:27.920 --> 17:30.380
And why did he do that?

17:30.380 --> 17:34.290
I don't know. He sometimes
does weird, nice things.

17:34.290 --> 17:37.170
Well, I-I could use
a refill.

17:37.170 --> 17:39.040
Tell your uncle
I said thanks.

17:39.040 --> 17:41.790
Hey, Max.
Let's go.

17:41.790 --> 17:42.710
Max: Yeah,
I'll be right there.

17:42.710 --> 17:43.790
All right.

17:47.120 --> 17:54.960
♪♪

17:54.960 --> 17:56.830
We got it.

17:56.830 --> 17:59.290
The grant for large-scale
invisibility optics --

17:59.290 --> 18:01.500
we got it --
full funding!

18:01.500 --> 18:03.330
-Amazing.
-I know!

18:03.330 --> 18:04.710
I can make
an airplane disappear,

18:04.710 --> 18:06.880
yet Reese still
chooses Kevin.

18:06.880 --> 18:08.330
Not at all following
what you're saying.

18:08.330 --> 18:10.080
I'm sorry.
It's stupid.

18:10.080 --> 18:13.540
Reese has this project, and
instead of doing it about me,

18:13.540 --> 18:15.880
she chose Kevin --
Mr. Fun Time --

18:15.880 --> 18:17.960
who basically just eats yogurt
all day long.

18:17.960 --> 18:19.580
I thought you liked having
your brother around.

18:19.580 --> 18:20.830
I do.
I love him.

18:20.830 --> 18:22.330
It's just, you know, this is
the story of my life, okay?

18:22.330 --> 18:23.500
I do all of
the hard work,

18:23.500 --> 18:27.000
and then Kevin swoops in
and everybody loves him.

18:27.000 --> 18:29.170
Don't be so hard on yourself.
You're really fun.

18:31.330 --> 18:33.170
I mean, I can't come up
with a specific right now,

18:33.170 --> 18:35.380
but generally speaking,
you are fun.

18:35.380 --> 18:37.670
I know that. Yeah.
I just need to remind Reese

18:37.670 --> 18:40.000
that I am not
all work, no play.

18:40.000 --> 18:43.120
I'm the perfect one-to-one
work-play ratio.

18:43.120 --> 18:46.040
Just...don't remind her
like that.

18:46.040 --> 18:47.380
Okay.

18:47.380 --> 18:48.420
Okay.

18:51.880 --> 18:53.710
[ Door closes ]

18:53.710 --> 18:54.790
Reese: Hello?

18:58.500 --> 19:00.670
Mom?

19:00.670 --> 19:01.960
Kevin?

19:03.830 --> 19:13.830
♪♪

19:13.830 --> 19:16.120
[ Insects chirping ]

19:16.120 --> 19:20.330
♪♪

19:20.330 --> 19:23.620
Hello?

19:23.620 --> 19:25.670
Reese!

19:25.670 --> 19:26.880
We're camping!

19:26.880 --> 19:29.380
Are you surprised?

19:29.380 --> 19:31.170
Yeah.

19:31.170 --> 19:34.580
We haven't gone camping in the
yard since I was like 10.

19:34.580 --> 19:36.710
I know. I know!
I've missed it, too.

19:36.710 --> 19:38.290
[ Chuckles ]

19:38.290 --> 19:41.500
I have, like, tons of
biology homework tonight.

19:41.500 --> 19:45.120
That's perfect --
biology under the stars.

19:45.120 --> 19:47.880
Come on.
It'll be fun.

19:47.880 --> 19:51.710
Just you and me, just us girls,
no pesky distractions.

19:51.710 --> 19:53.540
I found your
old sleeping bag.

19:53.540 --> 19:54.330
Come on!

20:02.790 --> 20:04.080
See, isn't this fun?

20:04.080 --> 20:05.380
Mm-hmm.

20:05.380 --> 20:06.670
Everyone thinks that Kevin's
the fun twin,

20:06.670 --> 20:09.330
but I know fun --
big time.

20:09.330 --> 20:11.540
Mom, did I do
something wrong?

20:11.540 --> 20:13.210
What? No. Why?

20:13.210 --> 20:16.210
You're just not
acting like you.

20:16.210 --> 20:18.750
[ Tent rustles, unzips ]

20:18.750 --> 20:20.000
Are we camping?

20:20.000 --> 20:22.620
-Yeah, but it's --
-I love camping! Incoming!

20:22.620 --> 20:24.120
[ Grunts ]

20:24.120 --> 20:26.580
I brought all those,
um, floor marshmallows.

20:26.580 --> 20:27.620
You want one?
-No.

20:27.620 --> 20:28.920
You?

20:28.920 --> 20:30.830
More for me.

20:30.830 --> 20:34.290
Did you know that I once fit 40
of these in my mouth at once?

20:34.290 --> 20:36.170
You can put that
in your report.

20:36.170 --> 20:38.920
Actually, don't, because I think
I could beat it tonight.

20:38.920 --> 20:40.420
[ Laughs ]

20:40.420 --> 20:42.750
[ Muffled ] I got a bigger mouth
now than I did.

20:42.750 --> 20:44.710
You've always had
a pretty big mouth.

20:49.750 --> 20:51.330
♪ Can you throw them over
your shoulder like a
Continental soldier? ♪

20:51.330 --> 20:52.330
♪ Do your ears ♪

20:52.330 --> 20:55.210
[ Deep voice ] ♪ Hang ♪

20:55.210 --> 20:58.920
[ Deeper voice ] ♪ Low? ♪

20:58.920 --> 21:00.790
Camping is so fun.

21:00.790 --> 21:03.880
Reese, did you know that
we used to come out here

21:03.880 --> 21:05.460
with our mom and dad?

21:05.460 --> 21:06.830
And it was a real
dumb idea, because --

21:06.830 --> 21:09.380
I don't know if you knew this --
but there was a serial killer

21:09.380 --> 21:10.380
in this town?

21:10.380 --> 21:12.210
Oh, yeah. Yeah,
I remember this.

21:12.210 --> 21:13.580
Mm-hmm.

21:13.580 --> 21:17.120
Yeah, it was very scary,
'cause he would wander around,

21:17.120 --> 21:20.790
maiming innocent victims
with a rake.

21:20.790 --> 21:23.250
No. No serial killers
use rakes.

21:23.250 --> 21:25.710
It was a sharp...

21:25.710 --> 21:27.790
sharp rake.

21:27.790 --> 21:31.710
It was as sharp
as an axe!

21:31.710 --> 21:33.790
It was an axe.

21:33.790 --> 21:35.170
And he would sneak up --

21:35.170 --> 21:37.620
Aah! Reese,
he's right behind you!

21:37.620 --> 21:40.120
Reese!

21:40.120 --> 21:42.580
Come on.
Are you made of wood?

21:42.580 --> 21:45.080
You know what we need?
We need s'mores.

21:45.080 --> 21:47.040
Come on.
Who doesn't love a s'more?

21:47.040 --> 21:48.290
[ Laughs ]
I'm on it.

21:50.500 --> 21:52.620
[ Clears throat ]

21:52.620 --> 21:55.000
Why haven't you
done it yet?

21:55.000 --> 21:56.170
What are you
talking about?

21:56.170 --> 21:57.960
Give the medicine
to Max.

21:57.960 --> 21:59.670
I did.

21:59.670 --> 22:01.500
Really?

22:01.500 --> 22:03.040
Huh.

22:03.040 --> 22:04.880
You better not be trying to get
out of our interview.

22:04.880 --> 22:07.540
I'm not.
It's just, I...

22:07.540 --> 22:09.000
I thought that was
the last thing.

22:09.000 --> 22:11.210
I must have
more work to do.

22:14.460 --> 22:16.040
How'd the handoff go?

22:16.040 --> 22:18.000
I don't know.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.120
Weird.

22:20.120 --> 22:22.580
All of his friends
were around.

22:22.580 --> 22:25.540
Oh. Were they jerks?

22:25.540 --> 22:28.880
No.

22:28.880 --> 22:31.790
But they were just
staring at me, like...

22:31.790 --> 22:33.210
[ Exhales deeply ]

22:33.210 --> 22:35.080
Like, "Who is this
random girl?"

22:37.960 --> 22:40.250
Is everything okay
at school?

22:40.250 --> 22:41.620
Yeah. It's fine.

22:43.420 --> 22:44.960
[ Clears throat ]
I want you to tell me

22:44.960 --> 22:46.960
what's going on, Reese,
so I'm gonna start

22:46.960 --> 22:49.830
shoving this marshmallow
into my nostril until you talk.

22:49.830 --> 22:51.250
Go ahead. Do it.

22:51.250 --> 22:53.080
I will do it.

22:53.080 --> 22:55.250
I wish there was
another way.

22:55.250 --> 22:56.750
Oh. Look.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.380
You're disgusting.

22:58.380 --> 22:59.330
Are you gonna tell me
what's going on?

22:59.330 --> 23:01.120
-Stop!
-There's only one way to stop --

23:01.120 --> 23:03.210
if you tell me...
tell me what's going on!

23:03.210 --> 23:04.620
[ Laughing ] Stop!

23:04.620 --> 23:05.540
[ Snorts, coughs ]

23:05.540 --> 23:07.250
Ugh!

23:07.250 --> 23:08.620
Okay.

23:12.540 --> 23:17.000
When my dad died, everyone
kept asking how I was doing.

23:17.000 --> 23:20.380
I just didn't want to talk
about it all the time.

23:20.380 --> 23:22.040
That's understandable.

23:22.040 --> 23:25.080
Except then I was the girl who
didn't want to talk to anybody.

23:26.880 --> 23:30.250
And is that true?

23:30.250 --> 23:32.210
Sometimes.

23:32.210 --> 23:34.500
Sometimes,
I don't want to be alone.

23:34.500 --> 23:36.380
Who wants a s'more?

23:36.380 --> 23:39.710
Mom, I'm sorry.
I really have to finish this.

23:39.710 --> 23:41.380
Okay.

23:41.380 --> 23:45.250
♪♪

23:45.250 --> 23:47.670
I'll have s'mores
with you.

23:47.670 --> 23:48.960
Thanks.

23:51.830 --> 23:53.620
[ Birds chirping ]

23:56.790 --> 23:58.670
What's all this?

23:58.670 --> 24:01.790
I forgot about this 401(k)
that I had.

24:01.790 --> 24:04.580
I can cash it out,
with a penalty.

24:04.580 --> 24:06.290
Why?

24:06.290 --> 24:08.330
Well, I figured,
once Max got his medicine,

24:08.330 --> 24:11.580
this would be over,
but still no vision.

24:11.580 --> 24:13.790
So, I think I'm supposed to
give away more money.

24:15.380 --> 24:17.000
Kevin!

24:17.000 --> 24:18.880
Plus, I have some stocks
I can sell.

24:18.880 --> 24:21.620
You have grown
so much.

24:21.620 --> 24:22.960
It's just money.

24:22.960 --> 24:24.750
[ Laughs ]

24:24.750 --> 24:26.500
Oh. Okay.

24:26.500 --> 24:29.210
Oh! Oh, I hate
these emotions.

24:29.210 --> 24:31.880
Every-- Everything is just
right at the surface,

24:31.880 --> 24:34.670
but I love that
you're doing this.

24:34.670 --> 24:36.080
[ Knock on door ]

24:40.290 --> 24:44.580
You stay away from my son,
and you stay away from me!

24:44.580 --> 24:47.710
I don't understand why you won't
take help for you son.

24:47.710 --> 24:49.330
You know, you think you're
a hero because you bought

24:49.330 --> 24:51.460
one month's worth
of insulin for Max?

24:51.460 --> 24:53.500
What about next month?
What about next year?

24:53.500 --> 24:55.210
Fine! I'll -- I'll buy it
as long as you need me to.

24:55.210 --> 24:56.500
You know, I don't need
your charity.

24:56.500 --> 24:59.380
You're just being stubborn.

24:59.380 --> 25:02.250
I work three jobs
to take care of Max,

25:02.250 --> 25:05.250
and I'm still almost
$30,000 in debt.

25:05.250 --> 25:07.540
And no matter how hard I try to
crawl back, it just gets worse.

25:07.540 --> 25:08.830
Wait. $30,000?

25:08.830 --> 25:13.120
That was basically the amount
of my severance check.

25:13.120 --> 25:15.750
Oh. Well, lucky you.
Have fun spending it.

25:15.750 --> 25:17.580
I already did.

25:17.580 --> 25:20.710
Wait, look, look, look, look --
I'm truly, truly sorry.

25:20.710 --> 25:24.250
I-I...

25:24.250 --> 25:27.000
I was just trying
to be nice.

25:27.000 --> 25:30.210
I'm sorry.
-It's fine.

25:30.210 --> 25:31.500
It's not your fault.
I, um...

25:34.500 --> 25:37.710
I guess I just needed an outlet
for all my anger.

25:37.710 --> 25:39.670
Well, I'm --
Just so you know,

25:39.670 --> 25:45.080
I'm always happy to get yelled
at, so you can vent away.

25:45.080 --> 25:47.210
I'm Kevin, also,
by the way.

25:47.210 --> 25:51.290
Emily.
I'm sorry.

25:51.290 --> 25:53.330
It's just all getting
a little overwhelming.

25:53.330 --> 25:56.420
My deadbeat ex took our son
off of his health insurance

25:56.420 --> 25:59.250
as revenge because Max
wanted to live with me.

25:59.250 --> 26:04.040
And I lost my insurance
when I changed jobs, so...

26:04.040 --> 26:05.830
I just keep opening up
credit cards.

26:05.830 --> 26:07.790
And now you can't climb
out of the hole.

26:07.790 --> 26:09.210
I don't care if I'm
a million dollars in debt.

26:09.210 --> 26:10.500
I'd do anything
for that kid.

26:13.040 --> 26:14.580
And I guess I shouldn't
be surprised,

26:14.580 --> 26:17.040
but Jason hasn't paid a penny
in child support, either.

26:17.040 --> 26:19.580
His own son? Mm.

26:19.580 --> 26:21.620
That's evil.

26:21.620 --> 26:23.080
He...

26:23.080 --> 26:25.540
doesn't sound great.

26:25.540 --> 26:27.580
That is a nice way
to put it.

26:27.580 --> 26:29.670
Tell her she'll get
her money back.

26:29.670 --> 26:31.750
Um...

26:31.750 --> 26:33.210
how?

26:33.210 --> 26:34.830
-What?
-[ Clears throat ] What?

26:34.830 --> 26:37.210
Just tell her.

26:37.210 --> 26:39.580
Breathe.

26:39.580 --> 26:40.880
Breathe.

26:40.880 --> 26:43.170
Okay. Just breathe.

26:43.170 --> 26:44.830
Are you having
a stroke?

26:44.830 --> 26:45.880
-Forget it!
-Ah --

26:45.880 --> 26:47.040
I know what to do.

26:48.710 --> 26:50.420
Ah...

26:50.420 --> 26:52.080
No. I have to go.
Um...

26:52.080 --> 26:53.380
We'll -- I'm --
We'll keep in touch.

26:53.380 --> 26:54.620
Thank you for --
Yes, I'm fine.

26:54.620 --> 26:58.960
I'm just --
There's, uh -- um [stammering]

26:58.960 --> 27:01.120
I'm gonna figure
some things out.

27:06.290 --> 27:07.500
Walnut Apple Crumble
for the lady,

27:07.500 --> 27:10.670
and for the constable --
pudding with a spoon.

27:10.670 --> 27:11.670
[ Laughter ]

27:11.670 --> 27:14.040
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

27:14.040 --> 27:15.540
[ Sighs ]

27:15.540 --> 27:17.750
So, I camped out
with Kevin last night.

27:17.750 --> 27:19.500
Mm! Roughing it.

27:19.500 --> 27:20.620
Yeah.

27:20.620 --> 27:21.710
And at first, I was
pretty mad at him,

27:21.710 --> 27:24.920
but, I don't know,
ended up having fun.

27:24.920 --> 27:26.290
What'd he do now?

27:26.290 --> 27:27.710
Nothing.

27:27.710 --> 27:30.920
I was just blaming him for
something that wasn't his fault.

27:30.920 --> 27:34.670
I was frustrated that I cannot
keep up with Reese's moods.

27:34.670 --> 27:36.120
I mean, one minute
we're best friends,

27:36.120 --> 27:38.620
and the next,
she's kicking me to the curb.

27:38.620 --> 27:39.540
Sounds about right.

27:41.250 --> 27:42.830
Think of yourself
when you were a teenager.

27:42.830 --> 27:45.170
I was perfect.

27:45.170 --> 27:46.540
I hung out with my mom
all the time.

27:46.540 --> 27:47.920
[ Scoffs ] All right.

27:47.920 --> 27:51.250
Well, think of any other
teenager in the entire world.

27:51.250 --> 27:53.500
I mean, they're complete
irrational jerks

27:53.500 --> 27:55.330
for like eight years.

27:55.330 --> 27:57.460
Just got to weather
the storm.

27:57.460 --> 27:59.500
No. No.

27:59.500 --> 28:01.500
I do not wait for problems
to solve themselves.

28:01.500 --> 28:03.170
Oh.

28:03.170 --> 28:05.500
I just need to figure out a way
to get into her head,

28:05.500 --> 28:07.580
you know,
get some common ground.

28:07.580 --> 28:10.290
I wish I could...
see into her brain.

28:10.290 --> 28:11.330
Uh, no, you don't.

28:11.330 --> 28:12.790
Yeah, I do.

28:12.790 --> 28:16.170
Look, I don't need her to tell
me everything, but...

28:16.170 --> 28:17.250
just basically
everything?

28:17.250 --> 28:19.330
[ Laughs ]

28:19.330 --> 28:21.380
Hmm.

28:21.380 --> 28:23.540
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
What's happening here?

28:23.540 --> 28:25.170
I can't try
your dessert?

28:25.170 --> 28:26.790
No. You can't just have
my pudding.

28:26.790 --> 28:28.500
That's...gross.

28:28.500 --> 28:29.500
Why?

28:29.500 --> 28:30.920
Pudding is basically
cold soup.

28:30.920 --> 28:34.170
I mean, would you eat
somebody else's soup?

28:34.170 --> 28:37.790
[ Laughs ] Sure?

28:37.790 --> 28:39.080
All right. Fine.

28:39.080 --> 28:41.210
[ Laughs ]
Have a taste.

28:41.210 --> 28:43.330
-Okay.
-I can't watch this.

28:43.330 --> 28:44.670
[ Laughs ]

28:44.670 --> 28:48.250
Looks like her ex-husband
lives her.

28:48.250 --> 28:49.710
Ooh.

28:49.710 --> 28:51.250
Are you feeling
all right?

28:51.250 --> 28:53.620
Got a little fired up
for a moment, but I'm good.

28:53.620 --> 28:55.460
You know, I never understood
road rage --

28:55.460 --> 28:58.000
calm one minute,
insane the next.

28:58.000 --> 28:59.670
Now I get it.

28:59.670 --> 29:01.960
Except you weren't driving,
so it was just rage rage.

29:01.960 --> 29:03.670
Well, it passed.

29:03.670 --> 29:05.500
Regardless, I think her
ex-husband is the key to this.

29:05.500 --> 29:07.670
Be kind.
Maybe he'll be kind, too.

29:07.670 --> 29:11.330
Hey, are you
Jason Owens?

29:11.330 --> 29:12.540
Why?

29:12.540 --> 29:16.330
I-I-I wanted to talk to you
about Max and Emily.

29:16.330 --> 29:19.120
[ Scoffs ] What's she
whining about now?

29:19.120 --> 29:22.040
She's -- She's not.
She just needs your help.

29:22.040 --> 29:23.290
Okay.

29:23.290 --> 29:24.210
-Yeah.
-But I don't want to help.

29:26.670 --> 29:28.330
[ Scoffs ]
Hey, come on, man.

29:28.330 --> 29:30.830
I mean, we're all
in this together.

29:30.830 --> 29:32.250
No, we're not.

29:32.250 --> 29:33.880
Tell Emily if she can't
afford the medicine,

29:33.880 --> 29:35.960
then maybe she shouldn't
have had a sick kid.

29:35.960 --> 29:37.920
[ Keys jostle ]

29:37.920 --> 29:38.750
[ Car door opens ]

29:41.040 --> 29:42.750
What the hell
are you doing?

29:42.750 --> 29:45.580
I am not sure.

29:45.580 --> 29:46.790
Make a fist.

29:46.790 --> 29:47.830
Uh, I don't really --

29:47.830 --> 29:49.170
Make a fist, now.

29:49.170 --> 29:50.210
Like this?

29:52.120 --> 29:54.080
Whoa! What are d--

29:54.080 --> 29:55.080
I am so sorry!
I'm --

29:58.000 --> 29:59.750
Can we talk about this?
Aren't we supposed to talk
about things like this?

29:59.750 --> 30:01.580
Enough talking!

30:01.580 --> 30:03.620
Aah! Ow!

30:03.620 --> 30:06.040
Okay. All right.

30:06.040 --> 30:07.500
[ Grunting ]

30:07.500 --> 30:08.500
I'm so sorry!

30:08.500 --> 30:09.500
Mnh-mnh!

30:09.500 --> 30:10.790
[ Yells ]

30:10.790 --> 30:12.620
Ow!

30:12.620 --> 30:14.380
[ Grunting ]

30:16.040 --> 30:18.960
I -- I really don't want
to be doing this,

30:18.960 --> 30:21.540
but I am,
and I can't stop!

30:21.540 --> 30:23.460
I'm sorry!

30:23.460 --> 30:26.120
[ Birds chirping ]

30:27.710 --> 30:30.670
Kevin? [ Sighs ]

30:30.670 --> 30:33.040
Kevin, will you please
say something?

30:33.040 --> 30:34.080
[ Knock on door ]

30:34.080 --> 30:36.670
-Mm!
-Kevin.

30:36.670 --> 30:37.670
Why are you
even asking?

30:37.670 --> 30:38.920
If I'm your
little puppet,

30:38.920 --> 30:40.290
why don't you just make me
talk to you?

30:40.290 --> 30:43.420
I'm sorry. I-I saw red,
and I couldn't control myself.

30:43.420 --> 30:46.080
So you controlled me instead?
Not cool.

30:46.080 --> 30:47.880
I've never done anything
like that in my life,

30:47.880 --> 30:50.750
and I've had a very,
very long life.

30:50.750 --> 30:53.120
I'm truly sorry.

30:53.120 --> 30:55.380
[ Doorbell rings ]
Do I have to keep worrying about
you flying off the handle now?

30:58.710 --> 31:00.000
I don't know.

31:02.210 --> 31:04.460
Kevin?

31:04.460 --> 31:09.880
Hi. I, um -- I brought you
some of your child support.

31:09.880 --> 31:12.380
What?

31:12.380 --> 31:14.580
I thought you were
just being crazy.

31:14.580 --> 31:16.750
I-Is there blood
on this check?

31:16.750 --> 31:17.880
[ Scoffs ]

31:17.880 --> 31:19.330
Should I ask?

31:19.330 --> 31:20.460
No.

31:20.460 --> 31:23.000
Uh, look, I know this
doesn't even come close

31:23.000 --> 31:26.670
to solving your problems,
but I am not giving up, okay?

31:26.670 --> 31:28.080
Okay.

31:28.080 --> 31:30.460
Okay.

31:30.460 --> 31:34.580
I, uh -- I've never met
anyone like you.

31:34.580 --> 31:36.920
Everything in my life
seemed dark and hopeless,

31:36.920 --> 31:40.250
and now
I see a tiny light.

31:43.330 --> 31:46.250
You mean me.
I'm -- I'm the light?

31:46.250 --> 31:49.210
-Yes.
-Okay. Just, uh, making sure.

31:51.540 --> 31:52.540
She means me.

31:52.540 --> 31:53.290
Oh, gosh.

31:58.460 --> 32:01.210
One milkshake.
Enjoy.

32:01.210 --> 32:03.790
I ordered a turkey wrap.

32:03.790 --> 32:06.120
Yeah, I know.
But you need a milkshake.

32:06.120 --> 32:07.290
I can tell.

32:07.290 --> 32:08.920
[ Whispers ]
It's my superpower.

32:10.710 --> 32:13.620
What's got you down?

32:13.620 --> 32:16.420
I'm writing a school paper
about Kevin.

32:16.420 --> 32:18.710
Oh, finally.
My boy's getting some ink.

32:18.710 --> 32:20.580
Can I read it?

32:20.580 --> 32:23.120
I mean, there's not much
to read.

32:23.120 --> 32:25.040
Said he was
"busy" today.

32:25.040 --> 32:26.330
So far,
I know he can stuff

32:26.330 --> 32:27.790
a bunch of marshmallows
in his mouth.

32:27.790 --> 32:29.880
Oh. How many?

32:29.880 --> 32:31.000
It's not important.

32:35.420 --> 32:37.880
Maybe I could ask you
some questions about Kevin.

32:37.880 --> 32:41.210
Ah, I don't know. I was kind of
saving for his Wikipedia page.

32:42.830 --> 32:44.960
But you're family,
so shoot.

32:44.960 --> 32:47.330
Okay.

32:47.330 --> 32:49.210
Do you have any idea
why Kevin would fill

32:49.210 --> 32:51.460
a stranger's prescription
for them?

32:51.460 --> 32:53.420
Hmm. Not sure.

32:53.420 --> 32:55.120
Kevin's always been
pretty giving.

32:55.120 --> 32:56.790
I remember,
back in high school,

32:56.790 --> 32:58.380
we had a teacher who got hurt
in this car accident,

32:58.380 --> 33:00.040
and he put together this whole
fundraiser for her --

33:00.040 --> 33:01.710
this big thing.

33:01.710 --> 33:04.460
Wow. I didn't know Kevin was
like that when he was younger.

33:04.460 --> 33:06.580
Oh, yeah. He got
the Engineering Team

33:06.580 --> 33:08.960
to volunteer
at this, uh...

33:08.960 --> 33:11.290
this...

33:11.290 --> 33:13.330
Hold up. [ Laughs ]

33:13.330 --> 33:15.580
Hold the phone.
Aw, man.

33:15.580 --> 33:17.540
Yep.
That wasn't Kevin.

33:17.540 --> 33:19.290
That was Amy.

33:19.290 --> 33:20.290
Amy?

33:20.290 --> 33:21.880
-Yeah.
-My mom?

33:21.880 --> 33:25.790
Yeah. All that stuff that
I said before -- that was Amy.

33:25.790 --> 33:28.380
In my defense, their mom used to
dress them alike all the time.

33:28.380 --> 33:31.330
It was this creepy
twin thing.

33:31.330 --> 33:33.710
I think you mom might actually
be my best friend.

33:33.710 --> 33:35.920
My mom did that?

33:35.920 --> 33:38.380
Yeah. She was great.

33:38.380 --> 33:39.830
You should write a paper
on her, too --

33:39.830 --> 33:43.500
like a, uh,
companion piece.

33:43.500 --> 33:45.380
I think I have enough
information.

33:45.380 --> 33:47.080
Thanks, Tyler.

33:47.080 --> 33:50.040
Oh, hey. Is it cool if
I finish your shake?

33:50.040 --> 33:50.960
Okay.

33:50.960 --> 33:56.380
♪♪

33:56.380 --> 33:57.710
Oh. Hey.

33:57.710 --> 34:00.170
Hi.

34:00.170 --> 34:02.750
Sorry.
What's your name again?

34:02.750 --> 34:05.710
Reese. Cabrera.
Reese Cabrera.

34:05.710 --> 34:07.540
Right. [ Chuckles ]

34:07.540 --> 34:08.960
You know, my mom said, at first,
she thought your uncle

34:08.960 --> 34:10.670
was a huge creep.

34:10.670 --> 34:14.330
But it turns out,
he's actually a good guy.

34:14.330 --> 34:16.750
He grows on you.

34:16.750 --> 34:21.210
Uh, hey, a-a couple of us are
gonna go see a movie tomorrow.

34:21.210 --> 34:22.750
You want to come?

34:22.750 --> 34:24.460
I don't know.

34:24.460 --> 34:27.670
Um...

34:27.670 --> 34:29.380
Okay. I'll come.

34:29.380 --> 34:31.420
Cool. Uh, we're gonna
meet there at about 5:00.

34:31.420 --> 34:32.960
Okay.

34:32.960 --> 34:34.670
-Bye.
-See you.

34:34.670 --> 34:37.380
[ Indistinct conversations ]

34:39.420 --> 34:45.120
I've got a hot take --
kindness is dumb.

34:45.120 --> 34:47.960
If I hadn't tossed away
all my money to random people,

34:47.960 --> 34:50.500
I'd have 30 grand --
exactly what Emily owes.

34:50.500 --> 34:52.000
I could've helped her
get back on her feet.

34:52.000 --> 34:55.080
But instead, I failed.

34:55.080 --> 34:56.500
You?

34:56.500 --> 34:59.210
I can't even control my emotions
enough to keep you safe.

34:59.210 --> 35:02.210
That's my only job.
[ Sighs ]

35:02.210 --> 35:05.080
Well, at least we can
be failures together.

35:05.080 --> 35:08.380
Hey, lip balm guy.
It's you.

35:08.380 --> 35:09.830
Yeah, I saw you over here
mumbling to yourself,

35:09.830 --> 35:11.000
and I didn't know
if I should, uh...

35:11.000 --> 35:12.290
-Oh.
-...interrupt. [ Laughs ]

35:12.290 --> 35:13.750
Yeah.

35:13.750 --> 35:15.500
I just had to stop
and thank you again

35:15.500 --> 35:16.500
for what you did
the other day.

35:16.500 --> 35:18.250
Oh. It was nothing.

35:18.250 --> 35:20.040
Made me smile
for the rest of the day.

35:20.040 --> 35:22.210
You know, if more people
did stuff like that,

35:22.210 --> 35:24.250
the world would be
a better place.

35:24.250 --> 35:26.500
Well, we can dream,
I guess.

35:28.420 --> 35:30.250
Well, if there's anything
I can ever do for you,

35:30.250 --> 35:32.790
just give me a yell, or at least
let me buy you a beer.

35:32.790 --> 35:34.580
[ Cellphone ringtone ]
♪ Hallelujah ♪

35:34.580 --> 35:37.830
Sorry. I thought I had that
on vibrate.

35:37.830 --> 35:39.710
"Rick Thomas,
Attorney at Law."

35:39.710 --> 35:41.830
Yeah. Two first names.

35:41.830 --> 35:43.420
It's tough to get a judge
to take me seriously.

35:43.420 --> 35:44.460
[ Chuckles ]

35:44.460 --> 35:46.330
Uh, you take care.

35:46.330 --> 35:49.000
"Specializing in medical
insurance litigation

35:49.000 --> 35:50.080
and claim denials."

35:50.080 --> 35:51.170
Mm-hmm.

35:52.920 --> 35:55.620
I have a friend who might
want to join us for that beer.

35:55.620 --> 35:56.880
Great.

35:56.880 --> 35:57.920
Right?

35:59.670 --> 36:01.710
Okay. Yeah.

36:01.710 --> 36:09.000
♪♪

36:09.000 --> 36:16.330
♪♪

36:16.330 --> 36:18.170
[ Amy scoffs ]

36:18.170 --> 36:20.290
When did you stop
being my little girl?

36:20.290 --> 36:27.000
♪♪

36:27.000 --> 36:28.500
[ Sighs ]

36:28.500 --> 36:34.540
♪♪

36:34.540 --> 36:37.170
Sure.
Kevin's a superhero.

36:41.880 --> 36:43.420
What?

36:43.420 --> 36:49.080
♪♪

36:49.080 --> 36:54.710
♪♪

36:59.210 --> 37:00.670
Mom, you home?

37:00.670 --> 37:01.710
Amy: In my room.

37:05.960 --> 37:07.920
I wanted to
talk to you.

37:10.000 --> 37:14.080
I was wondering if I could do
my history project on you.

37:14.080 --> 37:17.290
I only asked Kevin because
I just wanted to figure out

37:17.290 --> 37:19.420
what he was up to.

37:19.420 --> 37:21.830
Oh, I think we both know
what Kevin's been up to.

37:26.710 --> 37:28.460
That's my journal.

37:30.750 --> 37:34.120
When exactly were you gonna tell
me that you've been arrested?

37:38.920 --> 37:41.710
Okay, well, retroactive coverage
should be easy.

37:41.710 --> 37:45.540
And any bills that aren't paid
immediately we can appeal.

37:45.540 --> 37:48.750
That is incredible.

37:48.750 --> 37:49.830
Thank you.

37:53.330 --> 37:54.620
Thank you.

37:54.620 --> 37:56.830
All I did was buy
some lip balm.

37:56.830 --> 37:59.250
♪♪

38:00.620 --> 38:01.750
I want you to take
a look...

38:01.750 --> 38:03.620
[ Chuckles ]

38:03.620 --> 38:12.000
♪♪

38:12.000 --> 38:13.710
I'm gonna
use your bathroom.

38:13.710 --> 38:16.620
[ Grunts ]

38:16.620 --> 38:19.830
♪♪

38:19.830 --> 38:21.580
Hello?

38:21.580 --> 38:23.670
Can anyone tell me
where I am?

38:23.670 --> 38:26.460
[ Tiger growling ]

38:29.420 --> 38:31.830
Please don't
be there anymore.

38:31.830 --> 38:33.540
Please don't
be there any-- Oh.

38:35.670 --> 38:37.750
[ Growls ]

38:37.750 --> 38:44.750
♪♪

38:47.710 --> 38:49.170
[ Knock on door ]

38:49.170 --> 38:52.670
Emily: Kevin?
You all right?

38:52.670 --> 38:53.620
Emily?

38:55.830 --> 38:57.960
Yeah. You've been
in there a while.

38:57.960 --> 38:59.040
Do you need some Pepto?

39:02.750 --> 39:04.330
I'm okay.

39:04.330 --> 39:06.830
[ Exhales sharply ]
I'm okay.

39:06.830 --> 39:08.040
Everything...

39:10.580 --> 39:12.040
Oh.

39:12.040 --> 39:15.920
Everything is,
apparently, fine.

39:15.920 --> 39:20.710
Your friend is a miracle
worker...and so are you.

39:20.710 --> 39:23.540
I can't believe it.

39:23.540 --> 39:24.920
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:24.920 --> 39:26.500
[ Chuckles ]

39:29.000 --> 39:31.790
You're more than just
a tiny light.

39:31.790 --> 39:33.790
You're a medium-sized light,
at least.

39:33.790 --> 39:35.210
-Now, you're going too far.
-[ Laughs ]

39:35.210 --> 39:36.210
Did you need to --

39:36.210 --> 39:37.380
He's --
No, no. It's fine.

39:37.380 --> 39:39.000
You just --
How long was I in there?

39:39.000 --> 39:40.250
A long time.

39:40.250 --> 39:42.420
[ Bird chirping ]

39:42.420 --> 39:48.210
♪♪

39:48.210 --> 39:50.080
Come on, be happy.
We won.

39:50.080 --> 39:51.380
I am happy.

39:51.380 --> 39:53.250
And I'm exhausted.

39:53.250 --> 39:56.670
It's making me insane
to go from sadness

39:56.670 --> 40:00.120
to rage to happiness
to God knows what next. Whew!

40:00.120 --> 40:02.040
Most people go through that
before lunch every day.

40:02.040 --> 40:04.210
That's life --
highs and lows.

40:04.210 --> 40:05.620
How does anyone
get anything done

40:05.620 --> 40:07.500
with all this stuff
running through you?

40:07.500 --> 40:09.080
[ Scoffs ]

40:09.080 --> 40:12.460
Well, most of life is spent in
between, so you just remember

40:12.460 --> 40:16.210
that, when you're down,
that's temporary.

40:16.210 --> 40:18.040
And when you're up,
that's also temporary.

40:18.040 --> 40:19.920
And then, when you're
down again --

40:19.920 --> 40:21.710
So, you --
you saw a tiger?

40:21.710 --> 40:25.170
No. I was chased by a tiger
through a jungle.

40:25.170 --> 40:26.330
What do you think
that has to do with

40:26.330 --> 40:27.670
the other things
you've seen --

40:27.670 --> 40:30.880
butterflies, canoes,
a mariachi band?

40:30.880 --> 40:33.500
[ Sighs ] Well,
I don't think the Universe

40:33.500 --> 40:36.830
is trying to tell me
who the first righteous soul is,

40:36.830 --> 40:39.830
it's trying to tell me...
where.

40:39.830 --> 40:41.880
We'll keep working on it.

40:44.500 --> 40:46.500
But do you mind if
I sit out here for a moment

40:46.500 --> 40:50.170
until I settle into
an in-between place?

40:50.170 --> 40:52.170
Sure.

40:52.170 --> 40:55.120
I'm gonna ride this high
all the way to the pantry,

40:55.120 --> 40:57.500
see if there's any
new cereal.

40:57.500 --> 40:58.420
[ Laughs ]

41:01.670 --> 41:02.460
Reese.

41:04.960 --> 41:06.330
What's wrong?

41:06.330 --> 41:07.120
Kevin.

41:09.620 --> 41:11.880
You need to go upstairs,
pack your bags, and get out.

41:11.880 --> 41:17.500
♪♪

41:17.500 --> 41:22.960
♪♪

41:26.790 --> 41:34.830
♪♪

41:34.830 --> 41:42.960
♪♪

41:42.960 --> 41:51.040
♪♪

41:51.040 --> 41:59.120
♪♪
